node.text: Thank you Ben.
Christianity.....destroying lives century after century.

I’m using “get behind me Satan” here in the same thing way Jesus did when he said it to Peter in Mark 8:33 and Matthew 16:23.

Jesus predicted his own death and resurrection. But Peter like many was waiting for a military “strongman” messiah to overthrow Rome because that’s how he believed God would bring salvation to Israel. So Peter rebuked Jesus for daring to say he was going to die for everyone instead, even his enemies. Peter rebuked Jesus because you can’t overthrow Rome with a dead messiah.

Then Jesus said to Peter “get behind me Satan” to because Peter was tempting him with dominating others through political power in the same Satan had tempted him in the wilderness with power over all the earthly kingdoms. So Jesus rebuked him for acting that way and “for having the ways of the world” on his mind, rather than “the ways of God.”

I’m using that phrase in the same way towards the same kind of thinking within Christianity today.

“For the time will come when people will not tolerate sound doctrine and accurate instruction [that challenges them with God’s truth]; but wanting to have their ears tickled [with something pleasing], they will accumulate for themselves [many] teachers [one after another, chosen] to satisfy their own desires and to support the errors they hold” -2 Timothy 4:3-4

@jessicamcmasterlpc very very disturbing
👏🙏👏 I’m horrified at the amount of Christians who cherry pick the word in the Bible to justify their judgements and their lack of empathy…it’s disturbing on so many levels…

Having the people with the most influence or monetary power be the least empathetic amongst us is the exact reason why we face the biggest economical and social issues throughout history, and to this day.
@nicholasmurt tell that to those kids getting swooped by the ice from their schools.

You’d rather feed your children, ice cream, and chocolate, then healthy food. Because it makes them happy. You’d rather leave homeless people on the street rather than force them to clean up their bad habits. Because it makes them happy. You’re more empathetic than other people. You’re special.
I’d rather be empathetic than cruel. It’s an easy choice.

Truly. When I think about how much I’ve always cared about the environment and equal rights, I’ve always felt like I need to water down my stance on that stuff because it’s too “radical” for people, when to me it’s just common sense. Why is anger and hate and destruction more acceptable? I literally don’t get it
Yes and amen. Thank you for so simply and eloquently explaining what has been driving me crazy about “Christianity’s” relationship with the MAGA regime.

@_emeraldmax_ I agree 💯🙏 Just over 8 years ago I lost my parents to cancer, lost my place and ended up homeless at times, and I got diagnosed with hi and was 6 months to a year from dying and I haven't seen my siblings now in all of that time and barely any friends. Most of the love and support also went to rich men like Elon and Musk and Putin etc while someone like me struggled and had it ask for help and search it out to survive. They just get it handed to them.

@mister_mike_r I am so sorry you lost your parents and had to struggle so much 😞 People like you are stronger than any rich man in power. I am thankful you are still here, I know we don't know each other but if you need to talk I am here! I hope things get better ❤️

THIS!!!! The lack of compassion and empathy in our world right now is absolutely heartbreaking. There was a post on my local news about someone in our community that had established himself incredibly well, worked hard under a work contract in our city, and was well known and loved. Immediately, the comments were "should've came here legally". Our community member was ripped away from his family and our city, and you wanna talk about being "illegal". Wouldn't Jesus want to learn these people's stories? See what their goals are? Help them? Not throw them away. It's just baffling.
@lilyphoenix206 I'm a gay guy that was raised Catholic and to hear you and this man agree to this gives me a lot more hope at this time. 🙏🙌🙏
@mister_mike_r Glad you are both here ❤️
As a Muslim, this is so important to talk about! Thank you!!!
The Trump racism effect. 🤷🏻‍♂️
A strong sense of empathy is an indication of a higher level of consciousness. People with a higher consciousness aren’t easily manipulated and can’t easily be controlled by those in power.

@dancingsk3l3tons I am a U.S. citizen married to Belgian Citizen and I lived 16 years in Europe. America is not the Nation that helps out other Nations the most. America is the Nation that wants to dominate and benefit from every relationship with other Nation, not help. Europe has welcomed more immigrants and provided them with help and comfort more than America has in the past hundreds of years

Heard there's migrant grooming gangs all over England now too, you guys are awesome for letting them in 🙌

“The meek shall inherit the earth” has never resonated for me more recently. ❤️
@bethany_majeske I know a lot of recovering Catholics

@bethany_majeske I love this!! 🙏
I was raised catholic, I’m agnostic now. Your page has me listening to teachings of the Bible for the first time in over 20 years.  Thanks for doing what you’re doing.

@adubmiller definitely not, if you agree with this reel. The less fortunate are not the ones to blame, but the rich elite will make the lower classes fight amongst themselves while they keep getting richer.
Keep making these videos, Christians need to hear this, and from someone who looks like you. I will keep sharing these. Thank you for making a lot of us feel like we aren't going crazy.

It's interesting because the Bible or whatever text any religion/sect refers to, doesn't change, but things will magically stop "being a sin" one day. But then one day recently, they tell the men "beards are ok now and no longer a sin". Same for girls wearing pants. Unless someone is claiming to be a prophet and getting updates from god, I'm not sure how they explain that to the people. But he said you can't question or ask for clarification on anything.

For me, if it wasn't mainstream, we wouldn't have a 🍇felon for a president. Christians, real or faux, elected this person. The good Christians don't get a pass. 🤷🏽‍♀️

Well said.

@aimeejacksonjackson right now it’s not looking so good .. it looks arrogant, ignorant and intolerant, and very hateful.  And they wave that flag while trying uo rewrite the constitution and the history to suit their own agenda. .  We need to reclaim that symbol of what being patriotic really means.  It sickens me to see our flag  being synonymous with that patty.

caption.text:
I’m using “get behind me Satan” here in the same thing way Jesus did when he said it to Peter in Mark 8:33 and Matthew 16:23.

Jesus predicted his own death and resurrection. But Peter like many was waiting for a military “strongman” messiah to overthrow Rome because that’s how he believed God would bring salvation to Israel. So Peter rebuked Jesus for daring to say he was going to die for everyone instead, even his enemies. Peter rebuked Jesus because you can’t overthrow Rome with a dead messiah.

Then Jesus said to Peter “get behind me Satan” to because Peter was tempting him with dominating others through political power in the same Satan had tempted him in the wilderness with power over all the earthly kingdoms. So Jesus rebuked him for acting that way and “for having the ways of the world” on his mind, rather than “the ways of God.”

I’m using that phrase in the same way towards the same kind of thinking within Christianity today.

“For the time will come when people will not tolerate sound doctrine and accurate instruction [that challenges them with God’s truth]; but wanting to have their ears tickled [with something pleasing], they will accumulate for themselves [many] teachers [one after another, chosen] to satisfy their own desires and to support the errors they hold” -2 Timothy 4:3-4
